<div id="review_2319597044" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2319597044" />
    <a title="Mario the lone bookwolf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/78485297-mario-the-lone-bookwolf"><img alt="Mario the lone bookwolf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588320656p2/78485297.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2319597044?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mario the lone bookwolf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mario the lone bookwolf" href="/user/show/78485297-mario-the-lone-bookwolf">Mario the lone bookwolf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78485297-mario-the-lone-bookwolf?shelf=cronin-justin">cronin-justin</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2319597044" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16376828786512755559">One of the most amazing horror/fantasy novels I´ve read, combining splendid character design, very complex subplots, and amazing wordbuilding to something in the league of G R R Martin, King, and Sanderson.<br/><br/>That´s why professional creative writing matters<br/>This Iowa writers workshop Cronin studied in must be a wondrous place, enabling people to write like that. Cronin is a prime example of how the perfection of writing techniques can be learned because he studied and taught creative writing and tun</span>
  <span id="freeText16376828786512755559" style="display:none">One of the most amazing horror/fantasy novels I´ve read, combining splendid character design, very complex subplots, and amazing wordbuilding to something in the league of G R R Martin, King, and Sanderson.<br /><br />That´s why professional creative writing matters<br />This Iowa writers workshop Cronin studied in must be a wondrous place, enabling people to write like that. Cronin is a prime example of how the perfection of writing techniques can be learned because he studied and taught creative writing and tuned his work to perfection, culminating in this overkill.<br /><br />Finetuning and precision<br />It´s the intensity of the characterization, the many complex plots, and the always fine apocalyptic setting that make it a must-read. And there is still so much of it left in my memory after having read it a while ago, usually a very good sign that the stuff was of good quality. Another thing one realizes after finishing is how accurate plotting and planning can meet vivid protagonists and worldbuilding without any lengths in a brick of a book.<br /><br />Tastes differ, but it is a masterpiece. And Stephen King!<br />It´s a bit of a subjective field, because some seem to find the very detailed descriptions and the extent of the book too much, too wordy, not quick enough, not so greatly written, things King has to deal with too. But it kind of reflected his style so much that I must say that I am too heavily biased and possibly incapable to be objective about this one, because I like both the old, classic authors that inspired King and the new ones who name him as an inspiration, are suggested by him, or are compared with him. Kind of a King OCD obsession I definitively shouldn´t get checked because I have no freakings issues. It seems as if one has to be into that kind of writing style and very long books in general, if not, it could be a disappointment instead of a revelation. <br /><br />Even more King<br />This work has been compared with Stephen Kings´ The Stand and I must say that all together, the atmosphere, the plot, the characters, the intensity, the mega page-turning rage, make it worth to be compared with the grandmaster. I also couldn´t name a similar post apocalyptic book of that quality.<br /><br />And it has everything, apocalypse, post-apocalypse, pre-apocalypse, stylish monsters, evil scientists, little girls, nasty cliffhangers, and a dark tone that creeps out of each desperate page. Hardly ever so many dead trees flew by so quickly and the intensity of the works stays in reminiscence for a long time after finishing it. And it´s just the first part!<br /><br />Tropes show how literature is conceptualized and created and which mixture of elements makes works and genres unique: <br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePassage">https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.ph...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="16376828786512755559" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


